  <front>
    <title>BGPsec Validation State Unverified</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-borchert-sidrops-bgpsec-state-unverified-01"/>
    <author initials="O." surname="Borchert" fullname="Oliver Borchert">
      <organization>USA NIST</organization>
    </author>
    <author initials="D." surname="Montgomery" fullname="Doug Montgomery">
      <organization>USA NIST</organization>
    </author>
    <date day="15" month="April" year="2019"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>In case operators decide to delay BGPsec path validation, none of the
   available states do properly represent this decision. This document
   introduces "Unverified" as a well-defined validation state which
   allows to properly identify a non-evaluated BGPsec routes as not
   verified.</t>
    </abstract>
  </front>
</reference>